        <body>
            <p>The work presented by the authors is of good quality and deals with a very interesting research topic, regarding the recycling potential of PGMs from energy storage devices.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> The importance of recycling platinum group metals is stressed in this work and the economics are calculated for a prospective operating business. The authors have included a very well structured market analysis focusing on the main PGMs containing devices and have presented thoroughly the current status of the corresponding markets, the needs and the main drivers for wide utilization and exploitation.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> The methodological analysis the authors implemented for extracting meaningful results is well described and consists of basic elements of a business plan analysis. The adaptation of the business plan analysis elements is relatively thorough and financial data and analysis is presented to support the assessment made.</p>
            <p> Overall, the presented work is of good quality and addresses an emerging application with high potential for market deployment. The data extracted can be useful from a business operational perspective for the industrial ecosystem. However, there some additional points that require further clarification in an attempt to further support the decisions and assumptions made as well as to further enhance the quality of the manuscript.</p>
            <p> </p>
            <p> To this end the following are stated: 
                <list list-type="order">
                    <list-item>
                        <p>Important details regarding the market analysis which is presented in the manuscript are given without having being cited appropriately. The authors are encouraged to address this particular issue with proper referencing of the information obtained and used, while they also should stress and identify their own primary market research, if any.</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>In the SWOT analysis made in Table 1 the authors accurately state the alignment of the proposed effort with the EU strategies already in place. However, issues like minimizing resource dependence in the PGMs and promoting resilient raw material supply chains are not that clearly stated (contrary to the given business model canvas - BMC). Thus, this particular issue should be further commented on and analysed in the manuscript.</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>The authors are referring to the advantages of hydrometallurgical processes over pyrometallurgical ones. Also they state that this is the preferred technology for their approach. Nevertheless, this is not covered with additional details and although the financial plan section gives brief info regarding the materials/equipment used, the authors should clearly define the hydrometallurgical processes and concept used before the initiation and presentation of the BMC.</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>The authors' attention is required in Table 2 to clarify the values given (and commented within the manuscript body):</p>
                        <p> </p>
                        <p> (a) First of all it is advised that it should be re-written using digit grouping format (perhaps with the use of values in 1,000 &#x20ac; format), allowing the reader to clearly understand the data and numbers given.</p>
                        <p> (b) The final column giving the aggregation of the categories should be changed as CAPEX and OPEX data are aggregated which is not standard practice in the DCF analysis. If the values are presented, after their discounting (or with the use of WACC), this can be made but only in the OPEX data. After all the overall combined and discounted value of the project is given through the NPV value.</p>
                        <p> (c) Are the Depreciation and Amortization taken into account? There is a "Decreciations" category that appears to express general expenses but not any (linear?) depreciation of the CAPEX.</p>
                        <p> (d) Does the "total net profit" column express the yearly cash flow of the project?</p>
                    </list-item>
                </list>
